
Ordr.in JS API 		by Zain Alam

	A Javascript wrapper to interact with the Restaurant, User, and Order APIs provided by Ordr.in.

Usage

        Ordrin.initialize(api_developer_key, site_domain, jsonp_callback_function [if JSONP is being used]);
        
        var time = new Date(); // uses Javascript's built-in Date object
        time.setASAP(); // overrides Date properties to ASAP
        var addr = new Address("11111", "Middletown", "1 Main Street", "Apt #3E" [optional]);
        
        var subtotal = new Money("100");
        var tip = new Money("15");
        
        Ordrin.r.deliveryList(time, place, callback_function);
        Ordrin.r.deliveryCheck(restaurant_ID, time.convert, place, callback_function);
        Ordrin.r.deliveryFee(restaurant_ID, subtotal, tip, time, place, callback_function);
        Ordrin.r.details(restaurant_ID, callback_function);

Notes
	If a callback function is specified when initializing, the API will use JSONP. Otherwise it will default to assuming the presence of a reverse origin proxy. 
	Note that in the JSONP case, the name of the callback function in the initialize function and all others must be passed as a string.
	In the case of a reverse origin proxy being used the callback function's name is not passed as a string; just it's name.
		Ordrin.r.deliveryList(time, place, "callback_function");  // JSONP
		Ordrin.r.deliveryList(time, place, callback_function); // reverse origin proxy present
	
	User and Order APIs in progress.

